// E2E tests for control flow constructs
//
// NOTE: Control flow constructs like whileTrue:, whileFalse:, and timesRepeat:
// are implemented in the compiler but require variable bindings to persist
// across REPL expressions, which is a work in progress.
//
// These tests demonstrate the intended syntax. Full E2E testing of stateful
// control flow requires the REPL to support multi-line expressions or
// variable persistence across lines.

// ===========================================================================
// BLOCK CONTROL FLOW (single-expression tests)
// ===========================================================================

// Block that returns a value (no state change needed)
[5 + 3] value
// => 8

// Block with argument that returns computed value
[:x | x * 2] value: 7
// => 14

// Block with two arguments
[:a :b | a + b] value: 10 value: 20
// => 30

